      "side": 1,
      "message": "For a value that is not available, using NaN would not be correct. NaN is used to represent computation error or values that do not have a defined value like 0 divided by 0 is a NaN. As defined by IEEE 754 single precision floating point value this is represented as `s111 1111 1xxx xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx` where the bit represented by s is sign, 1 are the exponent, and x are for mantissa.\n\nBetter solution would be to keep sensorOperationalState as initializing and then on GetSensorReading update this parameter. Ignore the values when sensor is initializing.",
