      "writtenOn": "2026-04-14T08:49:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "`sensorOperationalState` comes from the `GetSensorReading` response — we can\u0027t just set it to initializing on our side, that\u0027s fabricating endpoint state.\n\nAlso, these are two different things. `sensorOperationalState` is internal PLDM protocol. The actual problem is that the D-Bus value (a double) sits at `0.0` before the first poll, and bmcweb/IPMI have no idea about `sensorOperationalState` — they only see the double. Setting our internal state to \"initializing\" doesn\u0027t fix the `0.0` on D-Bus at all.\n\n`NaN` for \"not yet read\" is already what this codebase does everywhere — offline terminus, unconfigured thresholds, failed/disabled sensors. updateReading() gates everything on std::isfinite(). We\u0027re just being consistent.\n\nOn the IEEE 754 point — that\u0027s about arithmetic semantics, not a rule against using `NaN` as a sentinel. Languages and libraries do this all the time.",
      "parentUuid": "9b64a27d_a8db589a",
      "revId": "09ce64a47937392a8dfa3c0488ac270273cb1fed",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
