      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-14T09:13:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If NaN is used at other locations, then for the consistency of the code, it would be fine. Treating a value not available yet as an imaginary number does not seem to be a right way of solving this problem. \n\nThere could be a corner case when the value computed by a sensor may result in an actual NaN (maybe due to some computation error). In that scenario how will the sensor reading help differentiate the error state and value not available state?",
      "parentUuid": "459aaf66_46ee60e7",
      "revId": "09ce64a47937392a8dfa3c0488ac270273cb1fed",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
